cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with a classification problem in computer vision, specifically in the context of zero-shot learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method that combines visual and semantic information, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a domain classification, which is a form of classification, and hence, it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with semantic representation, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses public benchmark datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
